<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-03-14T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-03-14T15:00:00-05:00" n="7" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d7">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">710.H/47: Telegram</note>
                                <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                            State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Brazil</hi>
                                        (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi></persName>)</head>
                                <opener>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-03-14T15:00:00-05:00">March 14, 1938—3 p.m.</date></dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>36. From the Under Secretary. Your 50, March 12, 11 a.m. [Here
                                    follows text of first three paragraphs of telegram No. 10, March
                                    12, 1 p.m., to the Minister in Uruguay, printed <hi rend="italic">supra.</hi>]</p>
                                <p>In any reply you make to the Brazilian Foreign Office you may
                                    repeat in general terms the views which I expressed to the
                                    Argentine Ambassador.</p>
                                <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>